# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# DATABASE (Server-side only) - Copy to .env
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Supavisor Connection Pooler Strategy (recommended 2025)
# Two connection strings needed for optimal performance:
#
# 1. DATABASE_URL (Transaction Mode - Port 6543)
#    - Used by Prisma Client for all database queries
#    - Uses Supavisor connection pooler for better scalability
#    - Get from: Supabase Dashboard → Project Settings → Database → Connection Pooling → Transaction mode
# Used by: apps/server (Prisma queries), packages/database
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://postgres.[PROJECT-REF]:[YOUR-PASSWORD]@aws-0-[REGION].pooler.supabase.com:6543/postgres"

# 2. DIRECT_URL (Session Mode - Port 5432)
#    - Used by Prisma Migrate for schema migrations only
#    - Direct connection without pooling (required for migration commands)
#    - Get from: Supabase Dashboard → Project Settings → Database → Connection Pooling → Session mode
# Used by: Prisma Migrate commands (migrate deploy, migrate dev, db push)
DIRECT_URL="postgresql://postgres.[PROJECT-REF]:[YOUR-PASSWORD]@aws-0-[REGION].pooler.supabase.com:5432/postgres"
